          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-07-15T18:09:18Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Keeping Oil and Natural Gas Flowing for Consumers Act</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) from proposing, implementing, or enforcing restrictions under the Clean Air Act on methane emissions from: (1) crude oil production; or (2) natural gas production, processing, transmission, and storage.</p> <p>The EPA may not finalize or enforce the proposed rule entitled, &quot;Oil and Natural Gas Sector: Emission Standards for New and Modified Sources,&quot; which proposes to amend the new source performance standards for oil and gas production by setting standards for methane and volatile organic compounds.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-11-17T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
